^-{ ^*BDeal of the Week 292 - April 15, 2002^*N
^*BBy Fred Gitelman^*N }
^-
This week's deal was the first deal played at the recent ^*BForbo Nations Cup^*N in Scheveningen, The Netherlands. I was on the North American Team (along with partner ^*BBrad Moss^*N and ^*BJohn Carruthers^*N-^*BHoward Weinstein^*N) that was invited to play in this event. The deal has been rotated to make South the declarer.

The Forbo tournament has been held every February for the past 10 years and during that time it has earned the reputation as one of the toughest and best-organized tournaments in the world. Unfortunately ^*BForbo^*N (a Dutch company that is a world-leader in linoleum products) has decided to withdraw the generous sponsorship that they have provided over the years. At this time the tournament organizers have not found another sponsor. Hopefully this will change.

There are 2 main events in the Forbo tournament. In the Nations Cup only 4 teams are invited and they play a complete round robin of 20-board matches over 2 days. Besides my team, the other 3 teams in the Nations Cup were The Netherlands, Italy, and Norway. Italy took first place honors and my team was lucky to win a tie-breaker with The Netherlands to capture second place.

The other main event at the Forbo is called the ^*BInternational Teams^*N and it is arguably the strongest Swiss Team event in the world. The field invariably consists of dozens of fierce teams from around the world and there are always plenty of dangerous Dutch teams in the field as well. Italy swept the 2002 Forbo by winning the International Teams as well as the Nations Cup. My team played the Italians in the last match for the win, but we lost that match and ended up 4th.|
