nt|
This was the second time that I played in the Forbo tournament (the last time was in 2001 when my team unexpectedly won the Nations Cup). Both of my experiences at the Forbo have been very positive. Not only has the bridge been first rate, but the hospitality and warmth shown to the players (especially by Chief Organizer ^*BElly Ducheyne^*N) really make this tournament special. 

I have said this before in past ^*BDeals of the Week^*N: Nobody knows how to run bridge tournaments as well as the Dutch! The world of bridge players can only hope that the organizers of the Forbo (and the ^*BCap Gemini^*N - another Dutch tournament that is currently without a sponsor) will find some way to keep these events going.

